canonical:
  title: 雨中感懷有作投擇之兼簡善之容齋酒熟曾有對床之約風雨可相負乎詩用夜飮韻二首
  author: 朴誾
  language: lzh
  text: 逢秋轉多思聽雨更懷人生死風塵裏詩書歲月因竹殘餘苦節楓老濕全身寂寞眞同調空簷謾自廵謾抱支離病俱爲潦倒人詩尊元有約風雨豈無因明日未可卜百年悲我身此懷曾領略徑進不逡廵
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 雨中感懷有作投擇之兼簡善之容齋酒熟曾有對床之約風雨可相負乎詩用夜飮韻二首
  author: 朴誾
  language: lzh
  text: 逢秋轉多思。聽雨更懷人。生死風塵裏。詩書歲月因。竹殘餘苦節。楓老濕全身。寂寞眞同調。空簷謾自廵。謾抱支離病。俱爲潦倒人。詩尊元有約。風雨豈無因。明日未可卜。百年悲我身。此懷曾領略。徑進不逡廵。
korean:
  title: 우중에 감회가 있어 시를 지어 택지에게 보내고, 겸하여 선지에게 편지하기를, 용재가 술이 익으면 서로 만나자는 약속이 있었으니, 비바람이 친들 저버릴 수 있겠는가 하였다. 시는 야음을 운으로 삼아 두 수가 있다
  author: 박은
  language: kor
  text: |-
    가을을 만나 더욱 생각이 많고
    비 소리 듣고 새삼 사람 생각한다
    생사는 풍진 속이요
    시서는 세월의 인연이다
    대는 쇠잔하여 괴로운 절개 남고
    단풍은 늙어 온 몸을 적시나니
    적막하기는 진실로 한가락인데
    빈 처마 밑을 부질없이 돌아본다
    부질없이 오랜 병을 앓고 있노라
    다 함께 요도(불행)한 사람 되었구나
    시와 술은 원래 약속이 있었지만
    바람과 비야 어찌 원인 없으리
    내일 일을 아무도 점치지 못하거니
    백 년을 산다 해도 내 몸이 아니다
    이런 생각을 일찍 짐작하였기에
    곧게 나아가 머뭇거리지 않네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1420_010_0830&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: 'Reflections in Rain: A Poem Sent to Taekji, With a Letter to Seonji, Since Yongjae Had Made a Promise to Meet When the Wine Was Ready—Can Wind and Rain Break Such a Bond? Two Poems on the Theme of Night Drinking'
  author: Park Eun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Autumn comes, and thought multiplies.
    Hearing rain, I think anew of those I know.
    Life and death drift in dust and wind,
    while poetry and books are the debt of years.

    Bamboo withers, leaving only bitter resolve,
    and maple ages, soaking through to the bone.
    In this solitude, a true harmony dwells—
    yet I pace beneath empty eaves for nothing.

    I hold this lingering sickness in vain,
    we have both become men of misfortune.
    Poetry and wine once held their promise,
    but wind and rain—do they come without cause?

    Tomorrow cannot be read by any art,
    and a hundred years cannot claim this body as mine.
    Having long foreseen such thoughts,
    I move forward without hesitation or turning back.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The poem alludes to a broken promise of meeting with friends (Yongjae) during a season of hardship, suggesting that external circumstances—both natural (wind and rain) and temporal (uncertainty of the future)—may prevent even the most sincere human bonds from being fulfilled.
  - key: ''
    value: 요도 (misfortune/adversity) reflects the Buddhist and Daoist concept of the world's transient nature and the inevitability of suffering.
